On the rocks is a medium space chic trendy, Unique club, bar atmosphere. There are two floors equipped with well stocked bars with all the best premium liquors. They have bottle service girls they are attractive, fun and attentive. The bar tenders are superior especially  Freda shes a bar manager ,the other girls are good too. The owners rock and mitch have created a Hookah Bar lounge with a high end club feel. They have a food menu that's not overwhelming  but a good selection of food from appetizers to entrees. It is a club so there are guest appearances from different celebrities and local talent. They do have a house DJ and they do guest Dj's on occasion.  The music  selection is vast, current and will definitely  get you hype and lit to party.Security is discreet, onpoint, and attentive to the surroundings. I went for the first time on H street Day. I was treated like a celebrity  they were giving away free shots from a liquor sponsor Hennessy. I had a both downstairs with my friends we popped bottles, smoked hookah and had mixed drinks and food. It was one of the best times I've had in a long time. Its definitely  a favorite  spot of mines to go. Trust me you'll feel the same way too.

Karaoke was fun. There weren't many people but it's a small space. The bartender struggled a bit but I think she was new. The drinks weren't great, but again, I think she was new. I was told that the original bartender/manager hadn't arrived. I still enjoyed myself a lot. The upstairs was terrible though. I guess it was supposed to be more of a club scene, but it was boring. Everyone sat around looking in each other's faces, and it was small. If you like karaoke, this is the place. If you want to go clubbing, this is not the place.
